Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian using the word "ubit" in different forms and positions:

1. On je *ubio* pticu kamenu sa svojim lukom. (He *killed* a stone bird with his bow.)
2. Ne želim *ubiti* ovu paučinu jer se bojim pauka. (I don't want to *kill* this spiderweb because I'm scared of spiders.)
3. Taj napadač je *ubijen* na licu mesta. (The attacker was *killed* on the spot.)
4. Mogu *ubiti* za čašu vode, toliko mi je žedno. (I could *kill* for a glass of water, I'm so thirsty.)
5. Ona je odlučila *ubiti* vreme gledajući filmove. (She decided to *kill* time by watching movies.)
6. Ako neko nešto uradi ovome detetu, *ubiću* ga. (If someone does something to this child, I will *kill* them.)
7. Njegove reči su *ubile* moje samopouzdanje. (His words *killed* my self-confidence.)
8. Kao šef projekta, moraš *ubiti* neke ideje i izabrati najbolju. (As the project manager, you have to *kill* some ideas and choose the best one.)
9. Tvoja bezosećajnost prema drugima može *ubiti* tvoj ugled. (Your insensitivity towards others can *kill* your reputation.)
10. Ovaj novi virus može *ubiti* milione ljudi ako se ne preduzmu mere predostrožnosti. (This new virus can *kill* millions of people if precautionary measures are not taken.)

I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.